    {
      "id": "c7e79e00_3ac0ba99",
      "file_path": "models-examples/src/main/resources/policytypes/onap.policies.native.Drools.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 67,
      "message": "I don't get this comment. Currently, serialization datatype is the entry of the \"serialization\" list which is ins dmaap_config datatype. And dmaap_config is the entry of the \"sourceTopics\"/\"sinkTopics\" list. In other words, each source/sink topic can have one or more serialization events. That's why I put serialization in a list.\n\nDo you suggest move source/sink topics under serialization datatype? If so, there would be duplicate topics under each serialization.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1441,
        "name": "Chenfei Gao",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "cgao@research.att.com",
        "username": "cgao"
      },
